# .dockerignore for the content-baked db image build.
#
# Resolved against the build context (content/runtime/) — the directory
# passed to `docker build`. Docker looks for `.dockerignore` in the
# build context root and recursively upward, so this file's location
# depends on where the build is launched from, not on this file's
# name. We launch `docker build content/runtime/` from the project
# root, so this file is the one docker reads.
#
# Rules are matched as Go-style filepath patterns:
#   `/audio`  — anchored to the context root: matches `audio/` only
#               at the top level of the context, NOT `seed/audio/`.
#   `foo`     — matches `foo` anywhere in the context (recursive).
#
# We add `/audio` as a guard rail: if someone ever changes the build
# context to `content/` itself (instead of `content/runtime/`), this
# rule keeps the persistent CMS working directory `content/.local/audio`
# out of the image. Currently the build context is `content/runtime/`,
# which has no top-level `audio/` (only `seed/audio/`), so the rule is
# a no-op today — but it documents intent and prevents future surprise.
/audio

# Future CMS working artifacts that may live alongside audio/. Same
# rationale — kept here so a future `docker build content/` doesn't
# accidentally bake secrets / caches into the db image.
